#Text=Christmas day bomber cooperating
#Text=Photo by US Marshal Service .
#Text=Image : E54987 .

#Text=The Nigerian man accused of trying to blow up a Detroit-bound jetliner on Christmas day with hidden explosives is cooperating with investigators and providing fresh intelligence after the U.S. enlisted the help of his family , an administration official said .
#Text=His family persuaded him to cooperate .
#Text=Umar Farouk Abdulmutallab
#Text=has been providing information to Federal Bureau of Investigation agents questioning him , the official told reporters on the condition of anonymity .
#Text=The official declined to provide details on what kind of information Abdulmutallab was providing .
#Text=Related news
#Text=" Failed bomb aboard Delta flight " — Wikinews , December 26 , 2009

column1: #Text=" Bomb plot accused ' co-operating ' " — UKPA , February 2 , 2010
#Text=Fire in Hyderabad hospital ; 1 dead
#Text=Somajiguda Somajiguda on the map of India

#Text=One person died and 41 were injured , including three nurses who are critically injured , in a major fire at Park Healthcare Hospital in Somajiguda , a suburb of the Indian city Hyderabad , on Tuesday morning .
#Text=The fire engulfed a major portion of the five-storey hospital ’s first floor , along with some medical equipment and furniture on the other floors .
#Text=City police commissioner A K Khan said that a criminal case had been registered against the hospital management .
#Text=" It is also being determined whether safety standards were followed by the hospital , " he said .
#Text=Sources
#Text=" Major fire at city hospital ; one patient dead " — The Hindu , February 2 , 2010
#Text=" Major fire at Hyderabad hospital ; one patient dead " — PTI , February 2 , 2010
#Text=China begins urgent sweep for tainted milk
#Text=Stripped shelves in a supermarket in China as a result of the contamination ( September 2008)Image : Kollision .

#Text=Chinese authorities say they are preparing to launch a crackdown on melamine -laced milk after the scandal over tainted products , which made hundreds of thousands of children ill two years ago and damaged China ’ s brand reputation overseas , resurfaced .
#Text=China has dispatched inspectors to sixteen provinces to urge local governments to thoroughly investigate cases concerning food safety .

#Text=The decision comes after milk products tainted with the industrial chemical melamine were removed from sale in Shanghai and the provinces of Shaanxi , Shandong , Liaoning and Hebei , the state-run Xinhua News Agency said .
#Text=Related news
#Text=" Contaminated baby 's milk induces wave of child illness in China " — Wikinews , September 22 , 2008

#Text=" China Begins Emergency Check of Dairy Products " — The New York Times , February 2 , 2010

column1: #Text=Karachi violence escalates , section 144 imposed
#Text=Map of Karachi , Sindh province
#Text=At least twenty-six people have been killed in Karachi , Pakistan after four days of ethnic killings , according to police officials .
#Text=The officials said that nine people were killed on Monday in the city 's Orangi western neighbourhood , which has a majority ethnic Pashtun community .
#Text=The Sindh government has awarded special powers to the Pakistan Rangers under Section 5 of the Anti-Terrorism Act 1997 and imposed Section 144 in the limits of 26 police stations for a month .
#Text=At least forty people were killed as ethnic clashes erupted across the city in early January .
#Text=Home minister of Sindh province , Dr Zulfiqar Mirza has called upon the Army to restore peace and order .
#Text=Sources
#Text=Salis bin Perwaiz .
#Text=" Rangers given control of 26 police stations " — The News International , February 3 , 2010
